This can be done using [Aggregation Pipeline](https://docs.mongodb.com/v3.2/core/aggregation-pipeline/index.html) as following

```
db.products.aggregate([
   {
        $unwind: &quot;$productfilter&quot;
   },
   {
        $unwind: &quot;$productfilter.attributeOptions&quot;
   },
   {
       $project: {
           &quot;specTitle&quot;: &quot;$productfilter.specTitle&quot;,
           &quot;specLabel&quot;: &quot;$productfilter.attributeOptions.specLabel&quot;,
           &quot;isDefault&quot;: &quot;$productfilter.attributeOptions.isDefault&quot;,
           _id:0
       }
   },
   {
       $group: {
           &quot;_id&quot;: &quot;$specTitle&quot;,
           &quot;specLabel&quot;: {$addToSet: &quot;$specLabel&quot;}
       }
   },
   {
    $project: {
        &quot;specTitle&quot;: &quot;$_id&quot;,
        &quot;specLabel&quot;: &quot;$specLabel&quot;,
        &quot;isDefault&quot;: &quot;$productfilter.attributeOptions.isDefault&quot;,
        _id:0
    }
   },
])
```

**Explanation:**

1. In first stage, the query [unwinds](https://docs.mongodb.com/v3.2/reference/operator/aggregation/unwind/index.html) the array `productFilter`; it means dividing the document in multiple records for each value of `productFilter` array item
2. In second stage it does the same for `attributeOptions` which was inside `productFilter`
3. [Project](https://docs.mongodb.com/v3.2/reference/operator/aggregation/project/index.html) stage, keeps the relevant fields from the document and names them for later purpose
4. [Groups](https://docs.mongodb.com/v3.2/reference/operator/aggregation/group/index.html) all documents now by `specTitle` and creates a new field &#39;specLabel&#39;(which utilizes [$addToSet](https://docs.mongodb.com/v3.2/reference/operator/aggregation/addToSet/index.html) to make an array from all different &#39;specLabel&#39; values.). As it&#39;s a set, it does not repeat the values if it&#39;s present.
5. Finally restructures the document as wanted. (Here I haven&#39;t included filters, genericFilter as per sample result because they are redundant but if you want, you can just edit the last stage `$project` to suit your needs

